+otherTeamPlaybooksHeader('Passing the Torch')
.sheet-PassingTheTorch.sheet-OPB
	input.sheet-triggerbox.sheet-ExpToggle(type='checkbox', name='attr_Toggle-Team-Moves-Unused', value='1', checked='')
	+move('PassingTheTorch-Move','<b>Lessons to Remember:</b> Once per mystery, each experienced hunter can narrate a brief flashback of them teaching or showing something to the fresh hunters, and hold 2. Any fresh hunter can spend 1 to get +1 forward to any roll.','share')
	+move('PassingTheTorch-Move','<b>Learning by Teaching:</b> Each fresh hunter takes a move from one of the experienced hunters’ playbooks, and each experienced hunter takes a move from one of the fresh hunters’ playbooks.','share')
	+move('PassingTheTorch-Move','<b>Sins of My Past:</b> One experienced hunter can state a wrong they did, or a thing they regret, and write it down. While this thing is written, the Keeper should introduce its nasty consequences when any hunter fails a move or spends Luck. Add “Did we compensate for the sin of the past” to your team’s end of mystery questions; if yes, the team gets an extra experience point; if yes (and it came up a lot) the team gets two extra experience and crosses out the sin. Once a sin is resolved, another experienced hunter can state their sin at the beginning of the next mystery.','share')
	+move('PassingTheTorch-Move','<b>Precious Youth:</b> When an experienced hunter becomes unstable, they get +1 ongoing to help out and protect all fresh hunters. When a fresh hunter becomes unstable, all experienced hunters get +1 ongoing to help out and protect them.','share')
	+move('PassingTheTorch-Move','<b>Forged in Rebellion:</b> When a fresh hunter goes directly against an experienced hunter’s orders or advice, each hunter involved in this scene marks experience.','share')
	+move('PassingTheTorch-Move','<b>Something Different:</b> Take a move from another team playbook.','share')
	+move('PassingTheTorch-Move','<b>Change Team Style:</b> Pick a new team style. You now use that one instead of the one you first chose.','share')